<font color="#FF0000">REMEMBERING AND IN HONOR</font><br>
<tt>Tue May  6  0:47:12 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
This is my first visit and in sitting here tonight I have cried for all who has given us so much and for those who has the memories of those whom they served with and lost.I used to work in a factory that made communication equip. and we had families who had loved ones over in Nam.We made care packages and wrote to them and sent packages to the orphanages.Little did I know that one of my sons would be there serving in the Marine Corps.When desert Storm came along we started a support group for the families and had a pancake breakfast and with the money we got wreaths for our 17 servicemen who lost their lives in Viet Nam they  were friends of my sons.When our middle school took them down I had a very good friend at the wall who helped the students with the wreath So Steve B if you read this Thank you so much.I helped with a serviceman who the government said could not have his name on the wall.I wrote several letters as he had to come home for a funeral and before he left Nam he had jumped in a hole that had a poison stick and he got infection,so when he came home at a later time and died. His name is now on the wall.I will be going to Findlay Friday May 9,1997 to put a wreath at the moving Ohio wall for our 17 dedicated service men who gave everything their life for us.<br>
Americans       
